sentences: Denial Ahmetović (born 26 February 1995)
is a Bosnian pop singer.
He was the winner of the fifth season of the televised singing contest Zvijezda možeš biti ti
(You Can Be a Star) on Hayat TV.
Early life ==
Denial Ahmetović was born in Zenica, Bosnia and Herzegovina, during the Bosnian War.
His first name is a version of "Daniel".
His father is Vehid Ahmetović and his mother's name is Adisa.
Ahmetović has a sister named Aldijana.
The Ahmetović family later relocated to Kakanj.

sentences: In 2012 Ahmetović auditioned for the fifth season of the televised Bosnian singing contest Zvijezda možeš biti ti on Hayat TV.
section: == Zvijezda možeš biti ti 5 and Cijeli moj svijet ==

sentences: He became the winner on 12 April 2013.
section: == Zvijezda možeš biti ti 5 and Cijeli moj svijet ==

sentences: Only one week after winning the contest, Ahmetović released his first single, "Nema ljubavi dok je Bosna ne rodi", on 19 April 2013.
section: == Zvijezda možeš biti ti 5 and Cijeli moj svijet ==

sentences: It was written by Marina Tucaković and Miligram musician Aleksandar Milić.
section: == Zvijezda možeš biti ti 5 and Cijeli moj svijet ==

sentences: His second song, "Cijeli moj svijet", written by Eldin Huseinbegović, was premiered 19 July 2013.
section: == Zvijezda možeš biti ti 5 and Cijeli moj svijet ==

sentences: His debut studio album Cijeli moj svijet was released on 23 May 2014.
section: == Zvijezda možeš biti ti 5 and Cijeli moj svijet ==

sentences: Personal life ==
Ahmetović was involved in a minor car crash on 31 December 2014 on the road to a New Year's Eve concert in Maglaj.
